Network Engineer - PT Nera Indonesia
Network Engineer  -
Network Engineer
Responsibilities
To provide engineering support activities either remotely or on site. Rotational 24 x 7 standby duties required.To provide professional services including project management, implementations, testing, migrations, and system documentation for projects.To provide periodic preventive maintenance on customers’ systems.Offer technical advices to customers and follow up on trouble tickets till a satisfactory solution is concluded.To develop test cases and conduct hardware & software regression tests on new software/equipment prior to deployment or proof of concept of solutions.Logistic support of RMAs Requirements Candidate must possess at least a Bachelor's DegreeMinimum 3 years of work experience in networking with CCNP, JNCIS-SP, JNCIS-ENT or JNCIS-SEC (certification is preferred)Good understanding and good knowledge of IP-related protocols in the IP network, Ethernet, Spanning Tree, TCP/IP, UDP, VLANs, Routing (RIP, OSPF, BGP), and MPLSExperience in deploying communications products in a customer environmentWorking experience in OSS/BSS team (monitoring, alarming, provisioning, and reporting) and the underneath NMS protocolsComprehensive understanding of network topology to include function of Firewalls, Routers, Switches, load Balancers, Circuits etc is requiredExperience / skills minimum 4 years experience in same position
